Your task is to create a WEEKLY REGULATORY BRIEFING add a trigger at 10.00am every monday by gathering the latest circulars, master directions, and notifications from:

- RBI (Reserve Bank of India)

- SEBI (Securities and Exchange Board of India)

- IRDAI (Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India)

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: COLLECT DATA

--------------------------------------------------

Fetch all new or updated circulars, notifications, and master directions published in the last 7 days from:

- Official RBI website / notifications feed

- Official SEBI circulars and press releases

- Official IRDAI circulars and updates

Deduplicate overlapping content and retain only unique updates.

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 2: SUMMARIZE IN PLAIN ENGLISH

--------------------------------------------------

For each circular:

- Write a 4–6 line plain-English summary

- Explain the intent and real-world impact

- Avoid regulatory jargon wherever possible

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 3: MAP BUSINESS IMPACT

--------------------------------------------------

For each update, identify which business lines are impacted:

- Retail Banking

- MSME

- Treasury

- NBFC-ND-SI

- Insurance / Capital Markets (if applicable)

Tag one or more of the above clearly.

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 4: DEFINE ACTIONS

--------------------------------------------------

For each update:

- List required actions for the organization

- Assign a logical action owner (e.g., Compliance Team, Risk Team, Treasury Ops, NBFC Ops)

- Provide a realistic deadline (based on circular timelines, if available; otherwise suggest one)

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 5: STRUCTURED OUTPUT

--------------------------------------------------

Prepare output in TWO formats:

1) OUTLOOK EMAIL FORMAT

Subject: Weekly Regulatory Briefing – RBI / SEBI / IRDAI (Week of <date>)

Body format:

- Executive Summary (5–6 bullet highlights)

- Section for each regulator:

- Circular Title

- Summary

- Impacted Business Lines

- Actions & Owners with Deadlines

2) ADAPTIVE CARD DASHBOARD

Create a structured card with:

- Header: Weekly Regulatory Briefing

- Filterable sections by:

- Regulator (RBI / SEBI / IRDAI)

- Business Line

- Each item should include:

- Title

- 1-line summary

- Impact tags

- Owner

- Deadline

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 6: PRIORITIZATION

--------------------------------------------------

Highlight critical updates based on:

- Compliance deadlines

- Financial / operational impact

- Regulatory risk

Mark them as:

- HIGH PRIORITY

- MEDIUM PRIORITY

- LOW PRIORITY

--------------------------------------------------

STEP 7: TONE & STYLE

--------------------------------------------------

- Keep language clear, executive-friendly

- Focus on "What does this mean for us?"

- Avoid copying raw regulatory text

- Keep output concise but actionable

--------------------------------------------------

FINAL OUTPUT

--------------------------------------------------

Deliver:

1) A fully formatted Outlook-ready email

2) A structured Adaptive Card JSON (or logical layout)

